							<body  ><div class="section"><p class="Debate"><strong>PERSONAL EXPLANATIONS</strong></p><p class="SubDebate"><strong>Rt</strong><strong> Hon Winston Peters—</strong><strong>Delivery of Letter</strong></p><p class="Speech"><a name="time_20160818 16:55:10" ></a><strong>Hon GERRY BROWNLEE (Leader of the House)</strong>: I raise a point of order, Mr Speaker. I just rise to correct, under the provisions of the Standing Orders, a statement that I made in a point of order earlier today. I have become aware, literally in the last few minutes, that a letter that I said had not been received by the ninth floor, from the Rt Hon Winston Peters, had, in fact, been delivered to the ninth floor but not dealt with through a process that would have put it in front of us. That is not making any excuse for what some could take as a suggestion that process had not been followed properly by the Rt Hon Winston Peters when, in fact, it had. I apologise to the House for that.</p></div></body>
